15:51.618 --> 15:54.913
How could they do this?

15:51.618 --> 15:54.913
I was telling the truth.

15:54.954 --> 15:56.997
I don't deserve

15:54.954 --> 15:56.997
to be treated this way.

15:57.039 --> 15:59.125
I didn't do anything.

16:01.085 --> 16:03.045
What didn't you do?

16:03.087 --> 16:04.422
[sighs]

16:04.464 --> 16:08.217
It doesn't matter,

16:04.464 --> 16:08.217
nobody believes me anyway.

16:08.259 --> 16:12.096
Not Uncle Jesse,

16:08.259 --> 16:12.096
not Joey, ugh, not even dad.

16:13.473 --> 16:15.558
[sobbing]

16:19.312 --> 16:21.522
I believe you, D.J.

16:25.568 --> 16:27.528
You do?

16:27.570 --> 16:30.949
Of course I do.

16:27.570 --> 16:30.949
You're my big sister.

16:30.990 --> 16:34.786
And besides that, you were

16:30.990 --> 16:34.786
looking right in my eyes.

16:34.828 --> 16:37.288
When you lie,

16:34.828 --> 16:37.288
you look at the top of my head.

16:39.833 --> 16:41.709
Thanks, Steph.

16:49.425 --> 16:52.553
I've gotta find a way

16:49.425 --> 16:52.553
for them to believe me.

16:55.348 --> 16:57.057
I can't believe

16:55.348 --> 16:57.057
this is happening.

16:57.099 --> 17:00.353
She's only 13

16:57.099 --> 17:00.353
and she's such a good kid.

17:00.394 --> 17:02.730
Danny, this could happen

17:00.394 --> 17:02.730
to any kid, there's..

17:02.772 --> 17:05.859
There's a lot of pressure

17:02.772 --> 17:05.859
on them to try drinking.

17:05.900 --> 17:07.527
I know,

17:05.900 --> 17:07.527
and not just from other kids.

17:07.568 --> 17:10.905
From, and it's sometimes

17:07.568 --> 17:10.905
these celebrities and rock stars

17:10.947 --> 17:12.532
and people

17:10.947 --> 17:12.532
these kids look up to.

17:12.573 --> 17:14.408
I mean, they're-they're making

17:12.573 --> 17:14.408
drinking look cool.

17:14.450 --> 17:16.202
I mean, they're sending

17:14.450 --> 17:16.202
the wrong message to kids.

17:16.243 --> 17:17.537
But I'll tell you something,

17:16.243 --> 17:17.537
D.J.'s gonna get

17:17.578 --> 17:19.205
the right message,

17:17.578 --> 17:19.205
okay, she's gotta know

17:19.246 --> 17:20.790
that there's no drinking,

17:19.246 --> 17:20.790
period, and I'd say we go

17:20.832 --> 17:22.041
upstairs and lay down the law.

17:22.082 --> 17:23.334
Jesse, wait a minute.

17:23.376 --> 17:25.753
Just sit down.

17:25.795 --> 17:28.422
I-I think it's not as simple

17:25.795 --> 17:28.422
as just punishing her.

17:28.464 --> 17:30.800
I think we have to find out

17:28.464 --> 17:30.800
why D.J. did it

17:30.842 --> 17:33.720
so we can decide

17:30.842 --> 17:33.720
the best way to help her.

17:33.761 --> 17:35.179
I just don't want her

17:33.761 --> 17:35.179
to be one of those kids

17:35.221 --> 17:36.514
who has to learn the hard way.

17:38.140 --> 17:39.559
Your attention, please.

17:39.600 --> 17:43.354
Whatever it is you said D.J.

17:39.600 --> 17:43.354
did, she did not do.

17:43.396 --> 17:45.439
- How do you know, Steph?

17:43.396 --> 17:45.439
- Because she was crying.

17:45.481 --> 17:47.525
And those were not

17:45.481 --> 17:47.525
I'm-in-trouble tears.

17:47.567 --> 17:49.903
Those were

17:47.567 --> 17:49.903
I-really-didn't-do-it tears.

17:49.944 --> 17:51.612
I think we have to straighten

17:49.944 --> 17:51.612
this out right now.

17:51.654 --> 17:53.364
- Yep.

17:51.654 --> 17:53.364
- She's not in her room.

17:53.406 --> 17:54.490
Where is she?

17:54.532 --> 17:55.742
She went back to the dance

17:55.783 --> 17:57.618
with Kimmy's mom

17:55.783 --> 17:57.618
to prove she's innocent.

17:57.660 --> 18:00.788
Oh, great, now she sneaks out

17:57.660 --> 18:00.788
of the house without telling us?

18:00.830 --> 18:02.582
What is going on with her?

18:02.623 --> 18:04.042
Look, you guys,

18:02.623 --> 18:04.042
I'll handle everything here.

18:04.083 --> 18:05.919
- Go ahead, take off.

18:04.083 --> 18:05.919
- Thanks, Joey.

18:05.960 --> 18:07.795
Bye, dad.

18:08.880 --> 18:11.090
I'll see you

18:08.880 --> 18:11.090
at school tomorrow. Bye.

18:12.425 --> 18:14.427
D.J., you missed everything.

18:14.468 --> 18:16.763
Kevin and Paul and Sam

18:14.468 --> 18:16.763
got caught drinking.

18:16.804 --> 18:19.181
They're gonna be suspended

18:16.804 --> 18:19.181
from school.

18:19.223 --> 18:21.935
I hate to say it,

18:19.223 --> 18:21.935
but they deserve it.

18:21.976 --> 18:25.271
Your mom's waiting outside.

18:21.976 --> 18:25.271
I have to find Kevin.

18:25.312 --> 18:27.607
He's over there waiting

18:25.312 --> 18:27.607
for his parents.

18:27.648 --> 18:29.067
You better talk to him now.

18:29.108 --> 18:31.485
You may not see him

18:29.108 --> 18:31.485
for a long time.

18:36.282 --> 18:38.576
- Hi.

18:38.618 --> 18:40.286
You and I have to talk.

18:40.327 --> 18:42.956
My family thinks I was drinking.

18:42.997 --> 18:44.331
Oh, man.

18:44.373 --> 18:46.709
You gotta tell my dad

18:44.373 --> 18:46.709
I'm innocent.

18:48.168 --> 18:50.212
Why did you have to go

18:48.168 --> 18:50.212
and drink, anyway?

18:51.422 --> 18:54.050
Those guys said

18:51.422 --> 18:54.050
it would loosen me up.

18:54.092 --> 18:56.886
I thought you'd have

18:54.092 --> 18:56.886
more fun with me.

18:56.928 --> 18:59.513
Well, I didn't have fun

18:56.928 --> 18:59.513
with you tonight.

18:59.555 --> 19:01.808
I had fun with the old Kevin.

19:04.685 --> 19:07.563
Kevin, your parents are here.

19:07.605 --> 19:09.816
I'm dead.

19:09.857 --> 19:12.234
D.J., I'm really sorry.

19:13.653 --> 19:14.988
I know you are.

19:19.158 --> 19:22.411
Is it okay

19:19.158 --> 19:22.411
if I call you again sometime?

19:22.453 --> 19:26.165
Alright, just make sure

19:22.453 --> 19:26.165
the old Kevin calls.

19:27.416 --> 19:29.376
Come on, son. Let's go.

19:33.297 --> 19:34.757
Kevin, have you seen D.J.?

19:34.799 --> 19:36.592
- Yeah. She's in there.

19:34.799 --> 19:36.592
- Thanks.

19:36.634 --> 19:39.303
- Uh, Mr. Tanner?

19:36.634 --> 19:39.303
- Yeah?

19:40.346 --> 19:42.932
D.J. wasn't drinking tonight.

19:42.974 --> 19:44.934
It was me and two other guys.

19:46.144 --> 19:47.937
She was trying to stop us.

19:50.356 --> 19:51.983
She was telling us the truth.

19:54.986 --> 19:57.530
I'm sorry, man. I-I saw her

19:54.986 --> 19:57.530
with the beer, I just--

19:57.571 --> 19:59.448
Oh, no, Jess, don't feel bad.

19:59.490 --> 20:01.200
It was an honest mistake.

20:02.869 --> 20:05.121
Thanks for telling us, Kevin.

20:05.163 --> 20:06.664
Come on, Kevin.

20:06.706 --> 20:08.624
Come on, let's go.

20:08.666 --> 20:10.877
I was pretty rough on her.

20:10.918 --> 20:14.296
Do you mind if I go in

20:10.918 --> 20:14.296
and have a word alone with D.J.?

20:14.338 --> 20:15.506
Okay.

20:21.345 --> 20:23.014
Hi.

20:23.056 --> 20:26.642
Oh, great.

20:23.056 --> 20:26.642
Now I'm in even more trouble.

20:26.684 --> 20:28.978
Look, I came down here

20:26.684 --> 20:28.978
to find Kevin so that--

20:29.020 --> 20:31.189
I just talked to Kevin outside.

20:31.230 --> 20:33.524
- You did?

20:31.230 --> 20:33.524
- Yeah.

20:37.820 --> 20:39.113
He told me what really happened.

20:41.115 --> 20:43.951
I owe you a big apology.

20:43.993 --> 20:45.995
You really hurt my feelings.

20:47.830 --> 20:50.083
I'm sorry

20:47.830 --> 20:50.083
for not believing you, pal.

20:52.292 --> 20:55.629
Well, I guess

20:52.292 --> 20:55.629
it did look kind of bad.

20:55.671 --> 20:58.925
And I did bend the truth

20:55.671 --> 20:58.925
a couple times this week.

21:01.010 --> 21:04.013
D.J., I want you to know

21:01.010 --> 21:04.013
why I lost my temper tonight.

21:06.724 --> 21:09.143
It just, it made me crazy

21:06.724 --> 21:09.143
thinking of my little niece

21:09.185 --> 21:11.145
out there starting to drink.

21:11.187 --> 21:12.855
I mean, this isn't fun

21:11.187 --> 21:12.855
and games, you know, I've seen

21:12.897 --> 21:14.148
it happen to my friends,

21:12.897 --> 21:14.148
they think they have it

21:14.190 --> 21:15.691
in their control,

21:14.190 --> 21:15.691
before they know it

21:15.733 --> 21:17.484
they'd messed up

21:15.733 --> 21:17.484
their whole lives.

21:19.278 --> 21:20.529
That's why I'm so proud of you

21:20.571 --> 21:22.281
for making

21:20.571 --> 21:22.281
the right decision tonight.

21:23.699 --> 21:26.368
It's not that hard to say no.

21:26.410 --> 21:29.247
Those kids

21:26.410 --> 21:29.247
were acting like idiots.

21:29.288 --> 21:31.040
Well..

21:31.082 --> 21:33.000
...we made it

21:31.082 --> 21:33.000
through tonight.

21:34.627 --> 21:36.629
The sad truth

21:34.627 --> 21:36.629
is that you're gonna be faced

21:36.670 --> 21:39.381
with a lot

21:36.670 --> 21:39.381
of tough decisions in your life.

21:39.423 --> 21:41.759
And not just about drinking,

21:39.423 --> 21:41.759
either, about..

21:41.801 --> 21:43.803
About drugs, and about sex..

21:43.844 --> 21:46.680
...and...who knows what.

21:46.722 --> 21:49.016
[dramatic music]

21:49.058 --> 21:50.977
I just wish

21:49.058 --> 21:50.977
you could grow up in a world

21:51.018 --> 21:53.062
where you can enjoy

21:51.018 --> 21:53.062
being a kid.

21:53.104 --> 21:57.024
But I'm sorry, pal,

21:53.104 --> 21:57.024
that's not the way it is.

21:57.066 --> 21:59.944
So...I hope that

21:57.066 --> 21:59.944
you'll use

21:59.986 --> 22:02.321
the same good judgment

21:59.986 --> 22:02.321
that you used tonight.

22:04.323 --> 22:06.200
Because I never want

22:04.323 --> 22:06.200
